[3] Sri Lanka
Date: Sat, 1 Apr 2006 10:44:36 -0500 (EST)
From: Alfonso Rodriguez, M.D.<ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>
Source: Daily News, Sri Lanka. 1 Apr 2006 [edited]
<http://www.dailynews.lk/2006/04/01/news40.asp>

An anti-dengue campaign is to be launched in the South to prevent the
spread of the deadly disease. A programme to destroy mosquito breeding
places and to keep the area clean will be launched by the Epidemiology Unit
in collaboration with the Government agents and medical officers in the
Southern Districts next week.
The campaign will commence from the South and will be expanded to Colombo
and the North and East districts. Over 500 workers will be engaged in the
cleaning of environment campaign and it will be completed within 2 months.
The campaign follows serious warnings issued by the health authorities
regarding an outbreak of a dengue epidemic in the country. Epidemiology
Unit Medical Officers told Lankapuvath that the number of dengue cases were
3-fold higher than in 2005.
They warned that if adequate measures are not taken by the Government, Sri
Lanka will face an epidemic very soon.
In the past 2 months 3 deaths have been reported from Kandy, Hambantota and
Jaffna. Medical Officer, Epidemiology Unit, Dr. Hasitha Tissera said 10
districts had been identified as the worst affected and measures were being
taken to carry out cleaning and awareness programmes before the end of the
next month.
